# UnoDOS/AppleII milestone-3 OutLast feasibility prototype: the pseudo-3D
# road racer at half-vertical-resolution (HANDOFF-M3 SS2, feasibility-gated).
# Run: ./build.sh test && python3 harness.py build/unodos_apple2_test.dsk shots < tests/m3_outlast.script
#
# Measured frame cost: one full road frame (28 bands grass+road+edges, car,
# HUD) is ~75k instructions ~= 0.24s ~= ~4 fps at 1 MHz - just under the
# 5 fps bar, but steering redraws immediately on each keypress (responsive).
# The verdict (README + PORTS-PLAN): SHIPS as a marginal prototype; a
# dirty-band repaint is the path past 5 fps.  ol_tick scrolls one step per
# soft-clock second; a full road redraw takes ~16 harness ticks.
wait 600
key right             # Clock->Files
key right             # Files->Theme
key right             # Theme->Dostris
key right             # Dostris->Pac-Man
key right             # Pac-Man->Music
key right             # Music->Tracker
key right             # Tracker->Paint
key right             # Paint->OutLast (row2 col1)
shot m3_outlast_select # OutLast icon highlighted
key return            # outlast_open: draw the road
wait 200   # disk-load: head seek + RWTS read
shot m3_outlast_road   # pseudo-3D road: grass shoulders, curve, car, Dist:0
wait 24
shot m3_outlast_scroll # road scrolled (stripes moved, Dist advanced)
key left              # steer the car left
key left
key left
wait 18
shot m3_outlast_steer  # car moved left; may run onto the grass (OFF ROAD!)
key esc               # back to the desktop
wait 24
shot m3_outlast_desktop
quit
